news.title: After original Chandigarh housing board allottees die, heirs need new licences
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said policy decision was taken about the transfer of small flats under Chandigarh Small Flats Scheme 2006, where both the allottees have expired after allotment.

news.title: Jharkhand: Over 4,000 PMAY-Gramin defaulters in Palamu to face heat
news.para: Most of the defaulters, sources said, have diverted the funds for some other purpose while some have built a portion of their house but now they are no longer interested in completing the construction.

news.title: Gurugram: Developer settles power infrastructure dues, discom to refund Ardee City residents
news.para: However, as DHBVN cannot refund in cash, the power discom has decided to add the amount collected from the residents as ‘development charges’ to their respective electricity account as advance payment so as to adjust the money against future power bills.

news.title: Basic Home Loan to disburse Rs 1,000 crore every month by March 2023
news.para: Basic Home Loan has aggressive expansion plan for 2022-23 and will be present in over 100 cities from about 30 cities currently.

news.title: NBCC to settle with home buyers of NBCC Green View
news.para: "..the company has decided to settle with all the homebuyers/allottees by way of buy-back of their flats/units and to do all such acts, deeds and things, necessary, incidental & ancillary to give effect to the same," NBCC said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Kapil Wadhawan sanctioned loans of over Rs 400 crore without following norms: CBI
news.para: The agency filed the additional charge sheet in the case of cheating against Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and Dewan Housing Finance Limited (DHFL) promoters Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan last month.

news.title: Relief from demolition unlikely for farmhouse owners in Noida
news.para: Over May and June, the Authority has demolished 124 farmhouses, including three clubs. It has also declared 1,000 farmhouses illegal and announced they would be demolished too.

news.title: Singapore's GIC to invest Rs 2,800 crore in Bhartiya Group's Bengaluru project
news.para: The Bhartiya Group will use the money to repay part of its debt, they said. "The firm has a debt of over Rs 1,000 crore against the commercial development," said one of the persons cited earlier.

news.title: Adani Group to buy land from K Raheja Corp for Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: In February 2021, Adani Group's flagship company Adani Enterprises entered into a 50:50 joint venture with EdgeConneX to develop and operate data centers throughout India.

news.title: More Chinese homebuyers refuse to pay loans amid contagion fears
news.para: Homebuyers have stopped mortgage payments on at least 100 projects in more than 50 cities as of Wednesday, according to researcher China Real Estate Information Corp. That's up from 58 projects on Tuesday and only 28 on Monday, according to Jefferies Financial Group Inc. analysts including Shujin Chen.

news.title: China property protests threaten to dent $220 billion of banks' mortgage loans
news.para: The mortgage bad-loan ratios for banks could rise three- to five-fold as a result of homebuyers stopping mortgage payments, analysts estimate, adding the protests will significantly add to lenders' risk exposure to the cash-starved property sector.

news.title: ACC's net profit down 60% to Rs 227 crore in Apr-Jun 2022
news.para: Total revenue from operations during the quarter under review was Rs 4,468.42 crore as against Rs 3,884.94 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Rising interest rates, inflation to affect affordable housing finance companies' growth: Report
news.para: Affordable housing finance (ticket size below Rs 25 lakh) has proven to be one of the most resilient sectors to economic cycles and seen rapid progress over the past decade, India Ratings and Research said in a report.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board auctions commercial plot in Jaipur for Rs 488 crore
news.para: ​​RHB (Rajasthan Housing Board) commissioner Pawan Arora said that the 45,632-square metre land between VT Road and Aravali Marg in Mansasorver was e-auctioned on Wednesday.

news.title: China banks, property stocks slump as homebuyers stop mortgage payments
news.para: Bonds of Chinese developers were also sold off, as confidence in the sector, already wrecked by the Evergrande Group crisis, continues to wane.
